Lemma 17: inv(add(inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))), inv(add(Y, inv(add(X, add(inv(Y), inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y)))))))))) = inv(add(X, add(inv(Y), inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y)))))).
Proof:
  inv(add(inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))), inv(add(Y, inv(add(X, add(inv(Y), inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))))))))))
= { by lemma 5 R->L }
  inv(add(inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))), inv(add(Y, inv(add(inv(Y), add(X, inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))))))))))
= { by axiom 1 (commutativity_of_add) R->L }
  inv(add(inv(add(inv(Y), inv(X))), inv(add(Y, inv(add(inv(Y), add(X, inv(add(inv(X), inv(Y))))))))))
= { by axiom 1 (commutativity_of_add) R->L }
  inv(add(inv(add(inv(Y), inv(X))), inv(add(Y, inv(add(inv(Y), add(X, inv(add(inv(Y), inv(X))))))))))
= { by axiom 1 (commutativity_of_add) R->L }
